bug.short_desc: [Gtk3] [Wayland] Detached toolbars have title drawn over content
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1164919 A screenshot of a detached LibreOffice toolbar
Description of problem: Once a toolbar is detached in LibreOffice running on wayland backend, the toolbar is overlapped by its title.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): libreoffice-5.1.3.2-7.fc24.x86_64 with gtk3-3.20.6-1.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Open any LibreOffice component (Writer, Calc, Base, â€¦) 2. Detach any toolbar by dragging it 3. Have a look at the toolbar, try to interact with it
Actual results: A title is drawn twice, once in window "decorations" and once in the toolbar, hiding some elements (see attached screenshot).
Expected results: Title only needs to be drawn in decorations, must not hide toolbar elements.

Created attachment 1164920 Screenshot of LibreOffice running inside weston
This issue is also present when running LibreOffice with Gtk3 inside weston. In this case, the toolbar is also cropped.
No, this issue is not fixed in 5.1.4.1-3.fc24, it is still present in libreoffice-5.1.4.2-1.fc24.x86_64.

(In reply to Christian Stadelmann from comment #2) > No, this issue is not fixed in 5.1.4.1-3.fc24, it is still present in > libreoffice-5.1.4.2-1.fc24.x86_64.
You probably meant libreoffice-5.1.4.2-3.fc24.
libreoffice-5.1.4.2-3.fc24 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 24. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-f2bf872a06

libreoffice-5.1.4.2-3.fc24 has been pushed to the Fedora 24 testing repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report.
